{{Infobox Artist Discography |Artist = [[Graveworm]] |Logo = |Image = Graveworm Metalcamp07 06.jpg |Caption = Graveworm performing in [[Tolmin]]. |Studio = 7 |Music videos= 2 |Video = 1 |EP = 2 |EP link = Demos and extended plays |Compilation = 1 | Option = 1 | Option name = Demo albums | Option link = Demos and extended plays | Option color = gainsboro |References = Yes }} The [[discography]] for [[Graveworm]], an [[Italy|Italian]] [[melodic black metal]] band, consists of one [[demo album]], two [[extended play]]s, seven [[studio album]]s, one [[video]] album and one [[compilation album]].
Graveworm got a record deal with Serenades records in 1997 before recording any material and then released their demo, their first extended play and studio album, ''Eternal Winds'' and ''[[When Daylight's Gone]]'', in the same year followed by their second extended play and their first video album, ''Underneath the Crescent Moon'' and ''Awaiting the Shining'', the year after. Towards the end of 1999 they released their second studio album ''[[As the Angels Reach the Beauty]]'' and then, in 2001, their third studio album ''[[Scourge of Malice]]'' alongside the joint re-release of ''When Daylight's Gone'' & ''Underneath The Crescent Moon'' later that year before singing to [[Nuclear Blast]] records. Their first release under Nuclear Blast was ''[[Engraved in Black]]'', their fourth studio album, in 2003. Two years later they released their fifth studio album, ''[[(N)utopia]]'', in 2007 their sixth studio album, ''[[Collateral Defect]]'' and in 2009 their seventh studio album ''[[Diabolical Figures]]''.
